==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heelpath
<hw>Heel"path`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called with a
play upon the words <ets>tow</ets> and <ets>toe</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
bank of a canal opposite, and corresponding to, that of the towpath;
berm.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark></p>

<p><q>The Cowles found convenient spiles sunk in the
<qex>heelpath</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>The Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heelpiece</ent>⟦br⟧
